cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.SOC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the analysis of information diffusion on Twitter, which is a social network platform.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the practical implications of the link between affect and virality, e.g. for viral marketing.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper may involve the development of classifiers or other software tools for analyzing the data.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possibility as the paper may involve natural language processing techniques for sentiment analysis.
- cs.SOC (Social and Community Informatics) is also a possibility as the paper discusses the social aspects of information diffusion on Twitter.
